Uses of Interface
de.fraunhofer.iais.eis.Message

    • Uses of Message in de.fraunhofer.iais.eis

      Subinterfaces of Message in de.fraunhofer.iais.eis 
      Modifier and Type Interface Description
      interface  AccessTokenRequestMessage
      Message requesting an access token.
      interface  AccessTokenResponseMessage
      Response to an access token request, intended for point-to-point communication.
      interface  AppAvailableMessage
      Message indicating that a specific App should be available (again) in the AppStore.
      interface  AppDeleteMessage
      Message indicating that an App should be deleted from the AppStore.
      interface  AppNotificationMessage
      Superclass of all messages, indicating a change of a DataApp.
      interface  AppRegistrationRequestMessage
      Message that asks for registration or update of a data app to the App Store.
      interface  AppRegistrationResponseMessage
      Message that follows up an AppRegistrationRequestMessage and contains the app registration confimation.
      interface  AppUnavailableMessage
      Message indicating that a specific App should be unavailable in the AppStore.
      interface  AppUploadMessage
      Message that usually follows a AppRegistrationResponseMessage and is used to upload a data app to the app store.
      interface  AppUploadResponseMessage
      Message that follows up an AppUploadMessage and contains the app upload confimation.
      interface  ArtifactRequestMessage
      Message asking for retrieving the specified Artifact as the payload of an ArtifactResponse message.
      interface  ArtifactResponseMessage
      Message that follows up a RetrieveArtifact Message and contains the Artifact's data in the payload section.
      interface  CommandMessage
      Command messages are usually sent when a response is expected by the sender.
      interface  ConnectorCertificateGrantedMessage
      Whenever a Connector has been successfully certified by the Certification Body, the Identity Provider can use this message to notify Infrastructure Components.
      interface  ConnectorCertificateRevokedMessage
      Indicates that a (previously certified) Connector is no more certified.
      interface  ConnectorNotificationMessage
      Superclass of all messages, indicating a change of a connector's conditions.
      interface  ConnectorUnavailableMessage
      Event notifying the recipient(s) that a connector will be unavailable.
      interface  ConnectorUpdateMessage
      Event notifying the recipient(s) about the availability and current configuration of a connector.
      interface  ContractAgreementMessage
      Message containing a contract, as an instance of ids:ContractAgreement, with resource access modalities on which two parties have agreed in the payload.
      interface  ContractOfferMessage
      Message containing a offered content contract (as offered by a data provider to the data consumer) in the associated payload (which is an instance of ids:ContractOffer).
      interface  ContractRejectionMessage
      Message indicating rejection of a contract.
      interface  ContractRequestMessage
      Message containing a suggested content contract (as offered by the data consumer to the data provider) in the associated payload (which is an instance of ids:ContractRequest).
      interface  ContractResponseMessage
      Message containing a response to a contract request (of a data consumer) in form of a counter-proposal of a contract in the associated payload (which is an instance of ids:ContractOffer).
      interface  ContractSupplementMessage
      Message containing supplemental information to access resources of a contract (e.g., resource access tokens).
      interface  DescriptionRequestMessage
      Message requesting metadata.
      interface  DescriptionResponseMessage
      Message containing the metadata, which a Connector previously requested via the ids:DescriptionRequestMessage, in its payload.
      interface  InvokeOperationMessage
      Message requesting the recipient to invoke a specific operation.
      interface  LogMessage
      Log Message which can be used to transfer logs e.g., to the clearing house.
      interface  MessageProcessedNotificationMessage
      Notification that a message has been successfully processed (i.e. not ignored or rejected).
      interface  NotificationMessage
      Event messages are informative and no response is expected by the sender.
      interface  OperationResultMessage
      Message indicating that the result of a former InvokeOperation message is available.
      interface  ParticipantCertificateGrantedMessage
      Whenever a Participant has been successfully certified by the Certification Body, the Identity Provider can use this message to notify Infrastructure Components.
      interface  ParticipantCertificateRevokedMessage
      Indicates that a (previously certified) Participant is no more certified.
      interface  ParticipantNotificationMessage
      Superclass of all messages, indicating a change of a particpants's conditions.
      interface  ParticipantRequestMessage
      This class is deprecated.
      interface  ParticipantResponseMessage
      This class is deprecated.
      interface  ParticipantUnavailableMessage
      Event notifying the recipient(s) that a participant will be unavailable.
      interface  ParticipantUpdateMessage
      Event notifying the recipient(s) about the availability and current description of a participant.
      interface  QueryMessage
      Query message intended to be consumed by a component.
      interface  RejectionMessage
      Rejection messages are specialized response messages that notify the sender of a message that processing of this message has failed.
      interface  RequestInProcessMessage
      Notification that a request has been accepted and is being processed.
      interface  RequestMessage
      Client-generated message initiating a communication, motivated by a certain reason and with an answer expected.
      interface  ResourceNotificationMessage
      Superclass of all messages, indicating a change of a resource.
      interface  ResourceUnavailableMessage
      Message indicating that a specific resource is unavailable.
      interface  ResourceUpdateMessage
      Message indicating the availability and current description of a specific resource.
      interface  ResponseMessage
      Response messages hold information about the reaction of a recipient to a formerly sent command or event.
      interface  ResultMessage
      Result messages are intended to annotate the results of a query command.
      interface  UploadMessage
      Message used to upload a data to a recipient.
      interface  UploadResponseMessage
      Message that follows up a UploadMessage and contains the upload confirmation.
